"title": "7258: promised land, early history of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7258: promised land, early history of",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The promise of a homeland, made to Abraham, began to unfold through Moses and Joshua. Moses taught that the land was to be held in trust by God's people, obedience to God's ways bringing blessing in the land and disobedience bringing his judgment.</p>\n<h2>The location of the promised land</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:18-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:18–15:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:1-Num34:12\">NUM 34:1–34:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:1\">DEU 7:1</a></p>\n<h2>Traditional descriptions of the promised land</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:17\">EXO 3:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num13:26-Num13:27\">NUM 13:26–13:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:7-Deut8:8\">DEU 8:7–8:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer32:22\">JER 32:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:6\">EZK 20:6</a></p>\n<h2>The promised land and Abraham</h2>\n<h3>The covenant with Abraham</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:7-Gen15:21\">GEN 15:7–15:21</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen13:14-Gen13:17\">GEN 13:14–13:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:7-Gen17:8\">GEN 17:7–17:8</a></p>\n<h3>The promised land given to Abraham's descendants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen12:7\">GEN 12:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:8\">GEN 17:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:7\">GEN 24:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod33:1\">EXO 33:1</a></p>\n<h3>A burial plot was Abraham's only earthly possession in the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:9-Gen25:10\">GEN 25:9–25:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen23:3-Gen23:20\">GEN 23:3–23:20</a></p>\n<h2>The promised land and the patriarchs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:2-Gen26:5\">GEN 26:2–26:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen28:12-Gen28:15\">GEN 28:12–28:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen35:11-Gen35:12\">GEN 35:11–35:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen50:24-Gen50:25\">GEN 50:24–50:25</a></p>\n<h2>Later generations look back to the promise made to the patriarchs</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut1:8\">DEU 1:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:13-Exod32:14\">EXO 32:13–32:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:20-Deut6:23\">DEU 6:20–6:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:7-Neh9:8\">NEH 9:7–9:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps105:8-Ps105:11\">PSA 105:8–105:11</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr16:15-1Chr16:18\">1CH 16:15–16:18</a></p>\n<h2>The promised land and Moses</h2>\n<h3>Moses is called to lead Israel into the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut10:11\">DEU 10:11</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:16-Exod3:17\">EXO 3:16–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod6:1-Exod6:8\">EXO 6:1–6:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:12\">NUM 11:12</a></p>\n<h3>A whole generation is not permitted to enter the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh5:6\">JOS 5:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num14:20-Num14:38\">NUM 14:20–14:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num32:9-Num32:13\">NUM 32:9–32:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:24-Ps106:27\">PSA 106:24–106:27</a></p>\n<h3>Moses and Aaron are not permitted to enter the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:12\">NUM 20:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num20:23-Num20:29\">NUM 20:23–20:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num27:12-Num27:14\">NUM 27:12–27:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:48-Deut32:52\">DEU 32:48–32:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut34:1-Deut34:4\">DEU 34:1–34:4</a></p>\n<h3>Moses' instructions to destroy the inhabitants of the land and their practices</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:16\">DEU 7:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:50-Num33:53\">NUM 33:50–33:53</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:1-Deut7:6\">DEU 7:1–7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:2-Deut12:3\">DEU 12:2–12:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut18:9-Deut18:12\">DEU 18:9–18:12</a></p>\n<h3>The instructions for distributing the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:54\">NUM 33:54</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num34:13-Num34:15\">NUM 34:13–34:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num36:5-Num36:9\">NUM 36:5–36:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh14:1-Josh14:5\">JOS 14:1–14:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:55\">PSA 78:55</a></p>\n<h3>Obedience to the law was a condition for enjoying the blessings of the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:1-Deut6:3\">DEU 6:1–6:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod20:12\">EXO 20:12</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:16\">DEU 5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev26:3-Lev26:12\">LEV 26:3–26:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:17-Deut6:19\">DEU 6:17–6:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:12-Deut7:15\">DEU 7:12–7:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:8-Deut11:15\">DEU 11:8–11:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:1-Deut28:8\">DEU 28:1–28:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:1-Jer11:5\">JER 11:1–11:5</a></p>\n<h3>Warnings not to forget God and follow Canaanite ways</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut11:16-Deut11:17\">DEU 11:16–11:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:12-Exod34:16\">EXO 34:12–34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev18:1-Lev18:5\">LEV 18:1–18:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:55-Num33:56\">NUM 33:55–33:56</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut8:10-Deut8:14\">DEU 8:10–8:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut28:15-Deut28:19\">DEU 28:15–28:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh23:14-Josh23:16\">JOS 23:14–23:16</a></p>\n<h3>Laws concerning the land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:23-Lev25:24\">LEV 25:23–25:24</a></strong> <em>The promised land is seen as belonging to God.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:10-Exod23:11\">EXO 23:10–23:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:1-Lev25:7\">LEV 25:1–25:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev25:8-Lev25:13\">LEV 25:8–25:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num35:33-Num35:34\">NUM 35:33–35:34</a></p>\n<h2>The promised land and Joshua</h2>\n<h3>Joshua is called to lead the Israelites into the promised land</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut31:7-Deut31:8\">DEU 31:7–31:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut3:28\">DEU 3:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:1-Josh1:6\">JOS 1:1–1:6</a></p>\n<h3>The Israelites enter the promised land and begin to possess it</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh3:14-Josh3:17\">JOS 3:14–3:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:16-Josh11:23\">JOS 11:16–11:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:43\">JOS 21:43</a></p>\n<h3>God's people are given rest</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh21:44-Josh21:45\">JOS 21:44–21:45</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut12:10\">DEU 12:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh1:13-Josh1:15\">JOS 1:13–1:15</a></p>",
